review_blob: Dark brown in colour. Smells of dark fruits. Strong alcohol tase with fruits. Very nice beer.
Light clear amber with a large white head. Grainy aroma with a light hoppy taste. Slightly bitter finish.
Amber beer with a nice white head. Nice malty hop aroma. Taste is a nice balance of hops and malt, with a bit of caramel. Nice beer.
Pours clear amber with a white head that quickly disappears. Smells like sour corn. Tastes like corn. Alcohol is overpowering. Poorly balanced beer.
Dark beer with a generous tan head. Has a sour grassy aroma to it. There is a slight cocoa and coffee taste to it initially but it has a sour finish.

beer_name: Dieu du Ciel Corne du Diable

review_blob: Very dark beer with a light brown head. Smells like overripe fruit, malts and scotch. Bitter fruity taste with a strong alcohol finish. Nice.
Dark red/orange beer. Small tan head that disappears quickly. Sweet roasted malt smell. Sweet malty taste as well with a slightly dry finish. nice beer.
beer_name: Sea Level High Street Wee Heavy Scottish Ale

review_blob: amber beer with an off white head. Citrus nose. nicely balanced hoppy taste.
beer_name: Sea Level Blue Heron Special Bitter

review_blob: Pours dark red/brown with a generous dark head. Smells like roasted malts. Taste is sweet and flavourful. Enjoyed this beer very much.
Dark amber ale with an off-white head. Aromas of nuts, malts and coffee. Nutty taste with a slight bitter finish.
Black beer with a tan head. Sweet malty, chocolaty aroma. Tastes of malt, cocoa and coffee with a bitter finish. nice.
beer_name: Sea Level Port in the Storm Porter

review_blob: Golden beer with a white head. Grassy malty aroma. Taste is sweet, with butterscotch and caramel. Pretty good beer.
Dark beer with a brown head. Smells of darkly roasted malts and coffee. Taste is a nice full flavour of chocolate, malts, and smoke. Very tasty beer.
Amber beer with a fine white head. Smells malty. Nice sweet malty flavour as well with a bit of citrus. Good taste.
golden beer with a white head. smells like straw and malts. taste is similar to the smell. Touch of citrus in the taste.
From bottle. Golden beer with big white head that disappears quickly. Sour fruit, and yeast aromas. Fruit and yeast are predominate in the flavour as well.
Clear golden beer with a small white head. Malt and floral aromas. Taste malty with a slight bitter after taste.
Amber beer with a white head. Smells floral and of caramel. Beer has a sweet bitterness.
Hazy orange beer with a small white head. Smells of fruit and spices. I taste a lot of peach in the beer. Its a nice flavour. Sweet, spicy, with peaches. nice.

beer_name: Dieu du Ciel Route des pices

review_blob: Dark red beer with a creamy head. Smells of sweet malts, caramels, and bit of chocolate. Tastes of dried fruits. Alcohol finish is a little too strong.
beer_name: Dieu du Ciel Rigor Mortis Abt

review_blob: Brown beer with very little head. Has a strong fruit aroma. Such as raisins, and overripe plums. Fruity taste with slight burn from the alcohol in the finish.
dark brown beer  with a tan head. Smells very fruity. Great flavour with a nice alcohol finish. Very enjoyable.
Hazy brown beer witha  small tan head. Aroma is sweet. Tastes sweet, with a hint of anise. Nice beer with a slightly alcohol finish.
Pale golden lager. Smells slightly malty. Tastes of slight malts and vegetables. Not very good at all.
Amber beer with white head. Smells sour. Not much taste. Unimpressive in every aspect. Bland.
Hazy brown beer with a small beige head. Smells of malt and fruit. Taste is malty caramel. Pretty good.
Jet black beer with a tan head. Smells of dark chocolate and coffee aroma. Coffee and chocolate come through in taste as well as roasted malts. Nice slightly bitter finish. Nice beer.
Golden beer with a fast disappearing head. Has an sour aroma. Malty taste. Slightly sweet. dry finish.
Pale beer with small white head. Smells bad. A sweet grassy scent. Very bland taste with no bitterness. gross.

beer_name: Dieu du Ciel quinoxe du Printemps

review_blob: Amber brown beer with a small head. Smells of caramel, and malts. Sweet malty taste. very slight bitter finish.
Pitch black beer with a generous head. Smells of malt, hops, and pine. Smooth beer with a slightly bitter bitter finish. Tasty beer.
Dark amber colour with a small tan head. Smells of molasses and spruce. Spruce is much more prominent in the taste. Not a strong alcohol taste at all, due to the overpowering taste of the spruce.
clear amber beer. Smells like a raspberry cereal bar. Raspberry is much more prominent in the taste. Overall, it is drinkable but nothing special.
Hazy amber colour with some sediment. Smells of spices and caramel. Sweet taste with a nice alcohol finish.
Red/amber beer with almost no head. Smells of caramel and malts. Tastes slightly smokey with caramel. Not bad.
Poured from bottle. Prominent apricot aroma. Taste is fruity, but kind of bland. Amber in colour with a white head that quickly disappears.
Poured from bottle. Nice dark brown body with a nut coloured head. Has a very metallic sour taste. Not very pleasant at all.  Expected much more from this porter.
hazy golden colour with large white head. Very malty smell. Nice carbonation. Sweet beer with a very faint bitter finish. nice.
Poured from bottle. Hazy orange/amber colour. Nice pale head. Aroma is malty with yeast. Taste is hoppy with an long bitter finish. Nice.
Nice amber colour with light coloured head that quickly disappears. Sweet malty aroma. taste sweet, slightly citrusy, with a light bitter finish. very good.
Bottle. Pours dark with very little head. Vanilla and chocolate flavours and aromas. Carbonation is light. Good beer.
On tap at The Loose Cannon in Halifax. Beer is brown with a head that quickly disappears. Has a malt smell. Lacking in flavour. Tasted very watered down.
On tap. Dark brown colour. Nutty and malty aroma. Nutty taste with a smooth finish. Slight bitterness. Light carbonation.
Bottled. Golden colour with white/orange head. Sweet floral,fruity, hoppy smell. Flavour is sweet, with a nice bitter finish. Overall this is a good IPA.
Beer is orange with white head. Sweet malty aroma. Taste is also sweet and malty but with a very slight bitterness to it.
Aroma is yeasty, and sour. Amber appearance with a white head. Taste as extremely bland with no body. Has a light texture, with average carbonation, and an abrupt finish. Overall, a very bland beer.
